This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation. It may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it involves the development of a deep network architecture. The use of color information from multiple color spaces suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the method on a skin lesion segmentation challenge suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
